 tThe changing meanings of lifelong learning policies: consequences for young adults and their life courses -- tTelling the story: exploring lifelong learning policies for young adults through a narrative approach -- tNavigating lifelong learning policies in Europe: impacting and supporting young adults' life courses -- tIndex0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aAvailable Open Access under CC-BY-NC licence. This comprehensive collection discusses topical issues essential to both scholarship and policy making in the realm of lifelong learning (LLL) policies and how far they succeed in supporting young people across their life courses, rather than one-sidedly fostering human capital for the economy. Examining specific yet diverse regional and local contexts across Europe, this book uses original research to evaluate differences in scope, approach, orientation, and objectives. It examines the embedding of LLL policies into the regional economy, the labour market, education and training systems and the individual life projects of young people, with a focus on those in situations of near social exclusion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAdult education and statezEurope. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aAlves, Natália, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmaral, Marcelo Parreira do, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenasso, Sebastiano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBouillet, Dejana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapsada-Munsech, Queralt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relato